    "body": "> Will be addressed with implementation of [status-im/status-go#3303](https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/3303)\r\n\r\nI'm afraid it won't be addressed with implementation of https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/3303 (or you have better solution?ðŸ™‚), i think we'd better add some validation for input password on the frondend side, some improvements we could do to improve user xp:\r\n- length of input password should >= 6 chars\r\n- when input password not valid, the button `Generate Scan Sync Code` should be disabled.. \r\n- add an extra input field to confirm input password\r\n\r\n this [PR](https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/3350) already added validation on local pair config, it also check if the passed password is empty. because passed password is encrypted with sha3(empty value can be also encrypted with sha3, corresponding sha3 value is 0xc5d2460186f7233c927e7db2dcc703c0e500b653ca82273b7bfad8045d85a470), just check password if is empty is not enough, it won't detect if original plaintext password is empty. Also i think it's not a good idea to add checks to see if password value is 0xc5d2460186f7233c927e7db2dcc703c0e500b653ca82273b7bfad8045d85a470 or some else sha3 value in the backend.\r\n \r\n @Samyoul \r\n ",
